	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well Valderessa, I read your message and I hope some of this advise helps for your Paladin.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ask your questions while playing...If you see a higher lvl Pally, send a tell or just blurt out your questions and other players may be able to respond.  I know that I do not come to this site and this is the first time that I visited the site but I would be more likely to play my character than come to this site on a regular basis.  Alot of other players may have alt char, including a Paladin.  Second, let people know in your group what your goals are...for example:  if you need more money to buy armor, let them know.  I have grouped too many times with people to take advantage of ffa looting.  Don't do this..people remember this and ignore your shouts of LFG.  Third, remember the purpose of the Paladin and stand at the front of the battle and enjoy your Paladin.  If you loot something you know another character needs, offer it to them without seeking compensation.  You will discover that they will remember your acts of kindness and will be there for your future needs.  I gave all my high quality ore to another char. for his skills, now he is enchanting platinum for my Paladin armor and another is helping me in my quests for ro armor.  I wish you best of luck and if you see me on line, please feel free to send me tell.  If I don't know the answer, I will help to find one.<br><br>Your fellow Pally, Astrial<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
