	   <tr><td colspan=2>The BP of Ro is NOT no drop. Consequently, your friend can make one for you if he has the components avaialable and just give it to you. <br><br>Since he is of a high enough level to obtain the Cauldrons, I would imagine he has plenty of MM granite as well. If he has melatite, then the rest should be easy.<br><br>Ronium is also NOT no drop. So you can make the ronium and give it to him and he can combine with the mold in the forge to make the BP and then give it back to you.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>As for a "Group" giving the Cauldrons to the Paladin in Rathe Mtns to get the mold (ie: one cauldron from him, one from you) I don't know if that would work, but if you TRY it and find out one way or another, please let us know!  I also don't know about a "Group" forging. Better to just give him the ronium bar you made and let him do it all. No reason to group forge.<br><br>Or, better yet, since he has plenty of them he obviously knows exactly how to do it. Get him to go back to MM with you and get you another Cauldron!!  Then you can do it yourself.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>32nd Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
