	   <tr><td colspan=2>Oh boy, Ghoulbane is probably the young paladin's wet dream, until you get it and have had it for 5 levels and see pallies 3 levels lower than you doing much more damage than you. How? you ask, its simple, GET A WURMSLAYER! The stats are better with 5 str and ok delay with great damage. With 125 str without yaulp 2, i do about 75 avg per hit. The proc on Ghoulbane is really nice because i almost always are fighting undead creatures, but it doesnt match up to 2 hits for 80 with ghoulbane continually. And in a group with haste on, i almost do as much damage as an even con monk without haste. Wurmslayer is a bit more expensive, going at 5k, but you can get it for 3k by buying all the scales and doing the rest of the quest. Im not bashing GB or anything, its a GREAT sword, one of the best pre-planes+kunark. Us pallies have it GOOD, we get a lot of choseable weapons, with some our own with great effects and the like. But once you get past level 35, trust me, you will hardly ever see a paladin with a GB that high level. About 95% of paladins that high up will have a wurmslayer or some good 2hander like a Mith 2hander. Just informing all of you young ones out there that it does get better!<br>Zomor-Bertoxx<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
