	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh, somehow people who turn out saying that Paladins do almost NO damage and have crappy spells are the ones that dont have extensive grouping experience and pretty much want to be better at soloing. Look here now, i absolutely LOVE my spells. I think that they are a great asset to our natural high defense abilities and our ability to absorb 2-3 times as much damage as a warrior or a SK or a ranger. We are the BEST class for staying alive, we are the hardest class to kill. Sure, you see all of those druids quad kiting dwarfs in BB, and then you suddenly see all 4 dwarfs die and the druids is not even touched, you may think " MAN, if only we could solo like that". Well, tell me this, if a druid gets hit by an even con or higher, what do you think is going to happen,are they going to be able to stay alive after getting stunned and then hit 5 times by 4 different things, HELL NO! Heh, druids and other casters may have an easier time soloing, but when it comes down to getting hit a couple of times by multiple things on your back while your running from a train, whos gonna live, the grouping paladin or the soloing druid? Heh, besides, im perfectly content with my soloing, pull, fight one maybe 2 blues, kill one, root, heal self, step back in and finish the job. Then, heal self till full, or if your lvl 39, cast regen on yourself, and med, repeat till ding. just like that. While the warrior who just killed 3 blues has to sit and wait for 30 minutes for his health to go back up, your out there killing stuff and getting MUCH better exp fighting small fights and medding a bit, than fighting big ones and medding for a long time. And at lvl 40, who cares about saving a groupmates life with a heal, thats the healer's job. I think that yes, we should get a little fighting bonus, just a little, like raising the cap per level on offense. That would make Paladins more acctractive, but still not able to be the best soloer. And since i fight undead almost every time i fight, nuking is no porblem for me, and if not, stunning/blinding is good too. The fact is, we are THE BEST DEFENDERS IN THE GAME, we are not supposed to do 50% of the damage in a group, we do minor heals while letting clerics med, we can pull, we can self buffs so not to waste others(cept shaman's) mana, we can partly nuke as to reduce fighting time, we can taunt, we ALWAYS HEAL THE CLERIC(hence, free rezzes when im on), and we can take most of the damage for the monks and rouges and rangers. If Verant made our fighting skills better, we would be a uber fighter, with the ability to solo like a god. And if they gave us better spells, we would be a crazy uber caster tank with the ability to beat the crap out of stuff and then root, nuke, heal self, med till root breaks, beat the crap out of MOB till dead. wow, i really droned on there didnt i, anyways, i think that paladins are perfect they way they are made, Verant did a great job, and i think that a paladin who is not having fun in the game is because of the way the person is playing him/her. oh and BTW, i can beat the crap out of a ranger the same level as me.Sorry about the longness of this post, ill try and keep it down next time. :)<br>Zomor-bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
