	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, at lvl 31, you can go to Lower Guk, without much success though, it is hard to get in a group there before lvl 34 or so. That is where the real good loot is, but you will not really have acsess to that until lvl 36 or so. Mistmoore is definatly a DANGEROUS zone to hunt in. You can take prolly 2 greenies on you without them getting past 75% of your health, but 3 is a problem. And since you will probably have to clear out the entire Pool area, which has about 15 spawns in it, some of which can be avoided, just to get to the Graveyard, where the real exp is. So DEFINATLY NOT Mistmoore in my view. I think that Frontier Mountains Giant fort is a good alternative. The exp there is horrible, but the loot is really worth the time spent on 1 yellow bubble(over 3 hours). The only real thing from FM that you can sell for good cash to other PC's are Forest Loops, and those are REAL rare. But the general sell to merchant stuff is great. Drops include weapons worth up to 44pp with indifferent faction, gems worth up to 10pp with indif. faction, words, runes, Forest Loops, some armor which sells for up to 44pp with indif faction, and about 2pp per corpse make up for the lack of real PC sellers dropping here. In 2 SLOW levels, you will probably make about 2-4k depending on luck of rolls, time spent on exp, and group sizes for exp intake. Another good area for your level is Unrest, My personal Favorite :). You will be able to get in a ghost group adn watch the exp fly by real fast. The loot here is pretty nice, since there is a merchant one zone across. Drops include Jagged Bands(real nice rings, go for 50pp each, common off ghost), Dwarven Work Boots(nice boots, go for 1k per, RARE drop off ghost), FS weapons, words, runes, 3pp per corpse, Savant's cap(common off of Magus), Dusty BS Gloves(rare off of Magus), BS mantle(common off of Kinght of Unrest), BS tunic(RARE off of Knight of Unrest), Opaline earrings(rare off of Undead Barkeeps), Thick Leather Apron(common off of Undead Barkeeps), *scratches head while thinking* Ahhh yes AND bronze armor peices. Not too shabby for a zone that is generally not real dangerous. And yes, at lvl 34 if the exp is slowing down, you CAN solo the Blood Pool for INCREDIBLE EXP to 36. Than Lower Guk or the dreadlands are good choices(Me going with Lguk).<br>Hope this helps.<br>Zomor-bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
