	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nice post Zomor. Mistmoore is definitely not the zone to run solo in. It is WAY too dangerous and difficult and on your own you probably couldn't even get past the ramp area.&nbsp;&nbsp;Solo you can pretty much forget about it unless there are other groups in the area that can help control the spawns.  (see my post below for more) <br><br>However, having said that, MM can be a GREAT, albeit, challenging zone in a group! You can attain the graveyard and have a good chance of holding it. And if you get brave and have a GOOD group with diverse classes, (enchanters are almost critical) you can venture into the Castle. NOTE: It's not easy. MM is a tough zone, but it can definitely be fun and will give you that PUCKER factor that you may not have had for a while! You can also have a decent chance of getting some MM granite with a good group and you are getting close to being able to camp the Ancille Cooks for the Cauldrons to get the BP of Ro, if you are so inclined, but I'd wait a few lvls first before trying this or have a VERY good group backing you up, with a good strategy.<br><br>Unrest is also very nice. Several of the rooms will provide you plenty of challenge and the XP is very good also.  The drops are okay and nothing fights undead like a Paladin!  I would recommend those two places if you really want to have some fun.  <br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>31st Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
