	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 5th 8:29 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, Axe of the iron back is a good weapon for level 16, and it is very commonplace now. It is good advice that you should have a nice 1hs and a nice shield to max out your skills with. Since you have a Lam. Blade, you may be able to trade that for a ghoulbane, or even the wurmslayer dragon scales( if you get a good deal) so you can do the Wurmslayer quest. If you do get one of these weapons, you will be ready to solo things that are up to 4 levels higher than you. <br><br>AHHHHHH Unrest, dungeon of many newbie's demises. One of the best mid level dungeons in ALL of Norrath. First, at lvl 16, you are ready to hunt there. You will probably need a group to gain exp at a fast rate. Yard trash probably cons low blue-green, so you will need to hunt inside the house, or pulling from the house. Now, Since many people do not know the art of pulling in Unrest, i reccomend you get a druid to, since they can cast harmony to get one mob out of a big group. Ghouls, Mummies, Dry bones, Dark bones are the mainstay of exp at this level. A good place to camp is the back door, a circular room with about 4 spawns in it. Pulling to here is quite easy, just get an Invis vs undead(ITU) and run on the bottom floor, pulling whatever you feel neccesary for good exp, just remember to pull small at first, so you can get small little fights instead of one HUGE one. Drops for your level include, common runes, words, some rare FS weapons, bronze weapons. he exp here at lvl 16 is not that good really, exp is much better at Highpass and Oasis. But Unrest offers Newbs the chance to get good at pulling, and the essential skills for grouping. On at lvl 20, you can now camp in the center room(s) and pull everything on the bottom floor no problem. These techniques should last you through lvl 24, where you can now begin to camp the second floor for GREAT EXP. Just be careful when you are there on dead hours, for the rooms up there are fairly hard to break into without a group at your lvl. Once you get up into the lvls as in lvl 30 or so, you can get into a ghost group and really find out why Unrest is such a blast to play. Great drops down here, plus a steady flow of exp make this camp one very fun one. <br>If you dont find Unrest to your liking, I would say that you should go to Highpass and get in a group. You will get very fast exp, and ok loot. This can get you up to lvl 20 or so, and you can hunt in Highkeep for several more levels. At about 23, i suggest going over to the Lake of Ill Omen, the BEST exp around. Since it is concidered a newbie zone, it gets an exp raise, and the amount of MOBS going about will insure you leveling VERY fast. you can ride the gobbo caves and the Sarnak fort till lvl 30 if need be. From there you may want to camp at Frontier Mountains for a couple of levels, than Lguk for a while. <br>Hope this helps.<br>Zomor-Bertoxx<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
