	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmmmm...soloing at lvl 30 in Mistmoore as a Paladin.&nbsp;&nbsp;Been there, done that...or should I say TRIED that and it is a very risky proposition indeed. Why? Because you can rarely just pull one mob there, and often times get 4 or even 5 at a time.  If one of those is a caster-type, you are in trouble. If 2 are casters, forget about it.  The pathing is difficult and the Mobs take circumferential routes to get to you when you pull them, thereby gathering friends along the way.  They are also very close to other mobs in small groups of 2 or 3.  Without a Harmony, pulling is very hard.  You can handle most anything that spawns in the Lake area (including the Gargs by the Tower) at lvl 30 and won't even get XP for some of it, but you will rarely get the benefit of one on one combat. <br><br>My solo success has been strictly confined to the Lake/Ramp area and usually when there were other groups there that helped control the spawns, giving me my own little pocket of mobs to mess with.  I have also been the ONLY one in the zone many times, standing at the top of the ramp, trying and trying and trying again to pull just one or two mobs from the first ledge.  I have tried lull (which sucks), I have tried soothe with very little success....some, but not much. I usually just make my pull, realize both Gargs and the two Initiates on the ledge both aggroed because my Lull or Soothe didn't work, they usually pull the other two near the lake and they ALL come running up the ramp. Time to zone out. One note, however, sometimes, the Gargs are the LAST mob to leave the zone once you've zoned out. So if you're lucky, you can zone back in and catch one remaining Garg and fight him one on one.<br><br>Like I say, you can handle anything that spawns in the entrance or even the Grave Yard and with a Wurm you are well-equiped and can handle two maybe even three of the lesser fighter types (Initiates, pledges and sentrys) on your own, but the Casters are bad news and interspersed with the fighter mobs.  MM is known for its DEADLY trains. The reason being, you don't get to fight just one at a time.<br><br>Solo as a 30th lvl Paladin,  my opinion is I wouldn't recommend it an it would be restricted to the Lake/Ramp area. Even the GraveYard is off-limits.  Even if you could get to the graveyard on your own (and the only way you would do this would be if a group cleared the way for you or someone gives you Invis) you would find it tough if not impossible to hold. You won't be able to fight your way there by yourself, that's for sure. Maybe you could purchase some Invis potions and get in and out that way if you've got the cash, which it appears you do since you are wielding a Wurmslayer! After the Graveyard, just about every place else is off-limits as well. The Ancille Valley, the Castle Entrance area, and most certainly the castle itself. Even if you could get to it, you would scarcely get a foot in the door before you died, unless invised.  I'm afraid you're going to need some help for many lvls to come in MM. <br><br>Just my humble opinion as a member of the 31st Circle of Dwarven Paladins and a Twilight Brethren. If you prove me wrong, PLEASE post and let me and others know how you pulled it off!<br><br>Kneesmasher<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
